occurrenceRemarks: This was an exciting encounter to me. I walked a couple of kms into the forest from the headquarters of Rara Avis. I stopped at stream crossing but remained hidden while I scanned for butterflies on the rocks. I saw movement on the opposite side of the trail and then realized that the mountain lion was approaching. It had not seen or heard me. It would have walked by me and I was concerned it might panic if it suddenly realized that I was there. I clapped once. The lion froze and then looked around to find the source. I raised the camera and managed this single shot before it raced away.
